oving and devoted wife mother and grandmotherin addition to her husband roosevelt she is survived by her children deborah phillips and her husband elijah of scranton roosevelt james jr of german gregory james of long pond her sisters maryjane wells of long island city new york and odessa williams and her husband warren of brooklyn new york her grandchildren brandy jamie james and mina maria james her greatgrandson brandon justice james and a host of nieces and nephews theresa was preceded in death by her brother john a levy and sister lillian mae sheriffthere will be a viewing from  to  am friday oct  at bolock funeral home  paradise valley road cresco the rev gary hughes will conduct a funeral service at  am at the funeral home burial will follow at fort indiantown gap national cemetery in annvillein lieu of flowers memorial donations may be made to pocono medical center attn pocono health foundation  e brown st east stroudsburg pa  or the dale and frances hughes cancer center  e brown st east stroudsburg pa bolock funeral home  crematory paradise valley road crescobolockfuneralhomecom subscribe now choose the plan that’s right for you digital access or digital and print delivery learn more james roosevelt i  wikipedia james roosevelt i from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from james roosevelt sr jump to navigation search james roosevelt i painting of james roosevelt at springwood estate in hyde park new york born july   hyde park new york us died december   aged  new york city new york us alma mater union college occupation businessman spouses rebecca brien howland m – her death sara ann delano m – his death children james roosevelt roosevelt franklin delano roosevelt parents isaac daniel roosevelt mary rebecca aspinwall relatives jacobus roosevelt iii grandfather grace walton roosevelt niece ellen crosby roosevelt niece james roosevelt roosevelt jr grandson anna eleanor roosevelt granddaughter james roosevelt ii grandson elliott roosevelt grandson franklin delano roosevelt jr john aspinwall roosevelt ii james with his son franklin in  james roosevelt i july   – december   known as squire james was an american businessman and horse breeder and the father of american president franklin delano roosevelt contents  early life  career  personal life  in popular culture  legacy  see also  references  external links early lifeedit roosevelt was born on july   in hyde park new york he was the son of businessman isaac daniel roosevelt – and mary rebecca aspinwall – isaacs parents were businessman and politician jacobus roosevelt iii and catherine welles his maternal grandparents were john aspinwall and susan howland in  james roosevelt graduated from union college in schenectady new york careeredit roosevelts business interests were primarily in coal and transportation he was vice president of the delaware and hudson railway and president of the southern railway security company personal lifeedit before his marriage roosevelt was considered an eligible bachelor tall slender and wealthy with considerable society connections in  he married his second cousin rebecca brien howland – they had one son james roosevelt rosey roosevelt – who married helen schermerhorn astor – four years after rebeccas death he met a sixth cousin named sara ann delano – at a party celebrating graduation of his distant cousin theodore roosevelt jr – from harvard university james and sara were married on october   and became the parents of franklin delano roosevelt – who married eleanor roosevelt – james reportedly was a good father to franklin but his recurring heart problems eventually made him an invalid franklin reacted by becoming fiercely protective of his father james died twenty years after he married sara and left the bulk of his estate to her and a modest inheritance to franklin he is buried at the churchyard at st james episcopal church in hyde park his grave is flanked by those of his wives in popular cultureedit roosevelt is voiced by john lithgow in the roosevelts a  documentary series by ken burns legacyedit in  franklin and sara roosevelt donated money to the town of hyde park for the construction of a new library named after james and still in use today see alsoedit biography portal referencesedit this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed april  learn how and when to remove this template message  miller nathan  theodore roosevelt a life   brands hw  traitor to his class new york ny doubleday p  isbn   external linksedit media related to james roosevelt sr at wikimedia commons v t e franklin d roosevelt nd president of the united states – th governor of new york – assistant secretary of the navy – new york state senator – presidency inaugurations st nd rd th new deal overview new deal coalition first  days second new deal federal emergency relief administration civilian conservation corps agricultural adjustment administration emergency banking act tennessee valley authority national labor relations act national industry recovery act public works administration national recovery administration works progress administration national youth administration social security act aid to families with dependent children communications act of  federal communications commission securities and exchange commission monetary gold ownership gold reserve act silver seizure record on civil rights defense industry nondiscrimination fair employment practices commission indian reorganization act executive orders   war relocation authority japanese american internment germanamerican internment italianamerican internment brownlow committee executive office of the president gi bill of rights cullen–harrison act roerich pact four freedoms four freedoms monument black cabinet jeffersons birthday holiday judicial courtpacking bill federal judicial appointments supreme court cabinet brai